8 “DEPARTMENT OF TRANSPORTATION
9
10 “SECTION 1. Not later than December 31, 2027, the Department of Transportation shall
11 report to the committees or interim committees of the Legislative Assembly related to
12 transportation on:
13 “(1) The department’s progress in implementing the recommendations resulting from the
14 audit required under section 1, chapter 1, Oregon Laws 2025 (special session).
15 “(2) The department’s progress in implementing transportation design practices as pro-
16 vided in ORS 184.748.
17 “(3) The department’s progress in establishing a department of transportation university
18 as required under section 6 of this 2026 Act.
19 “SECTION 2. Section 1 of this 2026 Act is repealed on January 2, 2028.
20 “SECTION 3. (1) The Department of Transportation shall create a database equivalent
21 to the Washington State Department of Transportation Gray Notebook.
22 “(2) The Department of Transportation shall report each calendar quarter to a committee
23 or interim committee of the Legislative Assembly related to transportation on the
24 department’s progress in creating the database.
25 “SECTION 4. Not later than December 27, 2027, the Department of Transportation shall
26 assess the needs of the department for training on best practices, including but not limited
27 to best practices for community engagement, project delivery and effective multimodal safety
28 design.
29 “SECTION 5. Section 4 of this 2026 Act is repealed on January 1, 2028.
30 “SECTION 6. The Department of Transportation shall establish a department of trans-
31 portation university, based on a survey of other state departments of transportation that
32 use a department of transportation university system.
33 “SECTION 7. (1) As used in this section:
34 “(a) ‘Highway’ has the meaning given that term in ORS 366.005.
35 “(b) ‘Transportation project’ has the meaning given that term in ORS 367.010.
