14 “SECTION 17. ORS 824.016 is amended to read:
15 “824.016. (1) The State Rail Rehabilitation Fund is established as an account in the General
16 Fund of the State Treasury. All moneys in the account are appropriated continuously to the De-
17 partment of Transportation for expenditures for any or all of the following:
18 “(a) Acquisition of a railroad line.
19 “(b) Rehabilitation or improvement of rail properties.
20 “(c) Planning for rail services.
21 “(d) Any other methods of reducing the costs of lost rail service in this state.
22 “(e) Rail projects, including:
23 “(A) Capacity improvements, such as:
24 “(i) New or lengthened sidings;
25 “(ii) Industrial spur rehabilitation; and
26 “(iii) Industrial spur construction;
27 “(B) Capital investments that improve safety; and
28 “(C) Capital investments that reduce greenhouse gases.
29 “(f) Providing state matching funds to leverage federal discretionary grant funding for rail
30 projects.
31 “(2) The program developed by the Department of Transportation under this section to provide
32 funds shall include:
33 “(a) Development of a methodology for prioritizing funding that takes into consideration an
34 applicant’s ability to use funding sources to leverage federal discretionary grant funding for rail
35 projects.
36 “(b) A requirement that rail projects selected are projects that are consistent with the goals of
37 the Oregon State Rail Plan.
38 “(3) The Department of Transportation shall provide funds under this section only with the ap-
39 proval of the Oregon Transportation Commission.
40 “(4) The department may use moneys in the fund to pay the department’s administrative costs
41 associated with the fund and with carrying out the provisions of this section.
42 “(5) Not later than December 31 of each even-numbered year, the department shall report, in the
43 manner provided in ORS 192.245, to the [Joint Committee on Transportation] committees or interim
44 committees of the Legislative Assembly related to transportation regarding the expenditures
45 of moneys in the fund and the status of rail projects that have received moneys from the fund.
