14 “SECTION 21. ORS 822.140 is amended to read:
15 “822.140. (1) To meet the requirement for local government approval of a dismantler certificate
16 under ORS 822.110 or a supplemental certificate under ORS 822.125, an applicant must comply with
17 any regulations established by a city or county under this section and must obtain the approval of
18 the governing body of the:
19 “(a) City, if the business is or will be carried on within an incorporated city of less than 100,000
20 population.
21 “(b) County, if the business is or will be carried on outside of any incorporated city.
22 “(2) A city or county governing body shall grant approval of a dismantler certificate [or
23 renewal] or a supplemental certificate when requested under this section if the governing body:
24 “(a) Approves the applicant as being suitable to establish, maintain or operate a motor vehicle
25 dismantling business;
26 “(b) Determines that the location or proposed location meets the requirements for location under
27 ORS 822.110;
28 “(c) Determines that the location does not violate any prohibition under ORS 822.135; and
29 “(d) Approves the location and determines that the location complies with any regulations
30 adopted by a city or county under this section.
31 “(3) The governing body of a city or county may regulate the expansion of premises or the es-
32 tablishment of premises at a new location under a dismantler certificate. An applicant must comply
33 with the regulations before the Department of Transportation may issue a supplemental dismantler
34 certificate. In adopting regulations under this subsection, a governing body:
35 “(a) Shall consider the extent of development of surrounding property as a residential area;
36 “(b) Shall consider the proximity of churches, schools, hospitals, public buildings or other places
37 of public gathering;
38 “(c) Shall consider the sufficiency in number of other motor vehicle dismantling businesses in
39 the vicinity;
40 “(d) Shall consider the health, safety and general welfare of the public;
41 “(e) May establish zones in which motor vehicle dismantling businesses are permissible and
42 other zones where they are prohibited; and
43 “(f) May prescribe limitations on the dimensions of the premises on which motor vehicle dis-
44 mantling businesses are conducted.
45 “(4) Regulations of a city governing body that are adopted under this section apply to motor
