1 “(2) ‘Qualified entity’ means the following:
2 “(a)(A) Counties in which no part of a mass transit district or transportation district exists; or
3 “(B) Intergovernmental entities who are providing public transportation services on be-
4 half of a county;
5 “(b) Mass transit districts organized under ORS 267.010 to 267.394;
6 “(c) Transportation districts organized under ORS 267.510 to 267.650; and
7 “(d)(A) Federally recognized Indian tribes; or
8 “(B) Intergovernmental entities who are providing public transportation services on be-
9 half of a tribe.
10
11 “CAPTIONS
12
13 “SECTION 24. The unit captions used in this 2026 Act are provided only for the conven-
14 ience of the reader and do not become part of the statutory law of this state or express any
15 legislative intent in the enactment of this 2026 Act.
16
17 “EFFECTIVE DATE
18
19 “SECTION 25. This 2026 Act takes effect on the 91st day after the date on which the 2026
20 regular session of the Eighty-third Legislative Assembly adjourns sine die.”.
